Nvidia recently launched its GeForce GTX Titan Xp, its most powerful gaming graphics card to date. The Titan Xp is powered by Nvidia’s Pascal architecture, which is built on a 16nm manufacturing process and includes the addition of high-speed GDDR5X memory. The release of the Titan Xp follows the recent launch of Nvidia’s GeForce GTX 1080 Ti graphics card. All GTX 10-Series graphics cards are based on Nvidia’s Pascal architecture and boast substantial performance increases over the company’s previous generation of GPUs. We have compared the specifications and pricing of Nvidia’s latest high-end GeForce GTX graphics cards – as detailed in the table below. South African pricing was taken from Rebel Tech, while there is currently no local pricing for the GTX Titan Xp. 